PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari is currently meeting with the former National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. Comrade Oshiomhole was taken to the President’s office by the Chief of Staff, Prof Ibrahim Gambari. The former APC Chairman’s mission at the Presidential Villa was not made public, but it may not be unconnected to the forthcoming governorship elections in Edo State. Vanguard PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari is meeting behind closed doors with the Vice President Yemi Osinbajo and the National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. December 27, 2018 In "News" NATIONAL Chairman of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole on Wednesday told President Muhammadu Buhari to rejig the security architecture of the country. July 24, 2019 In "News" PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari is currently meeting behind closed doors with the All Progressives Congress (APC) leaders and stakeholders from Benue State. November 23, 2018 In "News"